{
  "texts": [
    "This function provides the target value and is updated in a supervised way from the ST s stored in T M.",
    "Thus, this LSTM is also used to build a model to generate the compact structure of RT M from T M while seeking to learn the dynamics of ST s to provide better target values at the next agent update step.",
    "At each training time-step t, the authors define a transition by a tuple τ t = (s t, a t, r t, s t+1).",
    "Two transitions τ t 1 = (s t 1, a t 1, r t 1, s t 1 +1) and τ t 2 = (s t 2, a t 2, r t 2, s t 2 +1), t 1 = t 2, are similar (τ t 1 ≈ τ t 2) when the distance (e.g., Euclidean distance) between τ t 1 and τ t 2 is less than a threshold, that is, D(τ t 1, τ t 2) ≤ δ, in which δ is a threshold value of distance (or similarity).",
    "The N transitions that occurred up to a time instant are stored in T M and can be identified as subsets of similar transitions ST when the similarity condition is satisfied."
  ]
}